#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.84"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.84:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.84:0.2"
msgid "9. Theravagga"
msgstr "9. Senior Mendicants"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.84:0.3"
msgid "84. Tissasutta"
msgstr "84. With Tissa"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.84:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn22.84:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā tisso bhagavato pitucchāputto sambahulānaṃ "
"bhikkhūnaṃ evamāroceti:"
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Venerable Tissa, the Buddha’s paternal cousin, informed "
"several mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn22.84:1.3"
msgid "“api me, āvuso, madhurakajāto viya kāyo;"
msgstr ""
"“Reverends, my body feels like it’s drugged. I’m disorientated, the "
"teachings don’t inspire me, and dullness and drowsiness fill my mind. I live "
"the spiritual life dissatisfied, and have doubts about the teachings.”"

msgctxt "sn22.84:1.4"
msgid "disāpi me na pakkhāyanti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.84:1.5"
msgid "dhammāpi maṃ na paṭibhanti;"
msgstr ""

#. VAR: thinamiddhañca → thīnamiddhañca (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.84:1.6"
msgid "thinamiddhañca me cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.84:1.7"
msgid "anabhirato ca brahmacariyaṃ carāmi;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.84:1.8"
msgid "hoti ca me dhammesu vicikicchā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.84:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te "
"bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Then several mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "
"and told him what had happened."

msgctxt "sn22.84:2.2"
msgid ""
"“āyasmā, bhante, tisso bhagavato pitucchāputto sambahulānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ "
"evamāroceti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.84:2.3"
msgid "‘api me, āvuso, madhurakajāto viya kāyo;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.84:2.4"
msgid "disāpi me na pakkhāyanti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.84:2.5"
msgid "dhammāpi maṃ na paṭibhanti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.84:2.6"
msgid "thinamiddhañca me cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.84:2.7"
msgid "anabhirato ca brahmacariyaṃ carāmi;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.84:2.8"
msgid "hoti ca me dhammesu vicikicchā’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.107"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.84:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "So the Buddha said to a certain monk:"

# PTS has the usual satthā taṃ, āvuso sāriputta, āmanteti, which is presumably omitted by mistake in MS.
msgctxt "sn22.84:3.2"
msgid "“ehi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mama vacanena tissaṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantehī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Please, mendicant, in my name tell the mendicant Tissa that the Teacher "
"summons him.”"

msgctxt "sn22.84:3.3"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato paṭissutvā yenāyasmā tisso "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ tissaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” that monk replied. He went to Tissa and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn22.84:3.4"
msgid "“satthā taṃ, āvuso tissa, āmantetī”ti."
msgstr "“Reverend Tissa, the teacher calls you.”"

msgctxt "sn22.84:3.5"
msgid ""
"“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā tisso tassa bhikkhuno paṭissutvā yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
"Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ tissaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"“Yes, reverend,” Tissa replied. He went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down "
"to one side. The Buddha said to him:"

msgctxt "sn22.84:3.6"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, tissa, sambahulānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ evamārocesi:"
msgstr "“Is it really true, Tissa, that you informed several mendicants that"

msgctxt "sn22.84:3.7"
msgid "‘api me, āvuso, madhurakajāto viya kāyo … pe …"
msgstr "your body feels like it’s drugged …"

msgctxt "sn22.84:3.8"
msgid "hoti ca me dhammesu vicikicchā’”ti?"
msgstr "and you have doubts about the teachings?”"

msgctxt "sn22.84:3.9"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.84:3.10"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, tissa, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Tissa? "

msgctxt "sn22.84:3.11"
msgid ""
"rūpe avigatarāgassa avigatacchandassa avigatapemassa avigatapipāsassa "
"avigatapariḷāhassa avigatataṇhassa, tassa rūpassa vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā "
"uppajjanti sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"If you’re not rid of greed, desire, fondness, thirst, passion, and craving "
"for form, when that form decays and perishes, will it give rise to sorrow, "
"lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress?”"

msgctxt "sn22.84:3.12"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

# The Buddha’s incredible skill in teaching …
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.84:4.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, tissa."
msgstr "“Good, good, Tissa!"

msgctxt "sn22.84:4.2"
msgid "Evañhetaṃ, tissa, hoti."
msgstr "That’s how it is, Tissa,"

msgctxt "sn22.84:4.3"
msgid "Yathā taṃ rūpe avigatarāgassa …"
msgstr "when you’re not rid of greed for form."

msgctxt "sn22.84:4.4"
msgid "vedanāya …"
msgstr "feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.84:4.5"
msgid "saññāya …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.84:4.6"
msgid "saṅkhāresu avigatarāgassa … pe …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.84:4.7"
msgid ""
"tesaṃ saṅkhārānaṃ vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā uppajjanti "
"sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.84:4.8"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.84:5.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, tissa."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.84:5.2"
msgid "Evañhetaṃ, tissa, hoti."
msgstr ""

# An obvious typo here in anigata
msgctxt "sn22.84:5.3"
msgid ""
"Yathā taṃ saṅkhāresu anigatarāgassa, viññāṇe avigatarāgassa "
"avigatacchandassa avigatapemassa avigatapipāsassa avigatapariḷāhassa "
"avigatataṇhassa, tassa viññāṇassa vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā uppajjanti "
"sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"consciousness, when that consciousness decays and perishes, will it give "
"rise to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress?”"

msgctxt "sn22.84:5.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.84:6.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, tissa."
msgstr "“Good, good, Tissa!"

msgctxt "sn22.84:6.2"
msgid "Evañhetaṃ, tissa, hoti."
msgstr "That’s how it is, Tissa,"

msgctxt "sn22.84:6.3"
msgid "Yathā taṃ viññāṇe avigatarāgassa."
msgstr "when you’re not rid of greed for form."

msgctxt "sn22.84:6.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, tissa, "
msgstr "What do you think, Tissa? "

msgctxt "sn22.84:6.5"
msgid ""
"rūpe vigatarāgassa vigatacchandassa vigatapemassa vigatapipāsassa "
"vigatapariḷāhassa vigatataṇhassa, tassa rūpassa vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā "
"uppajjanti sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"If you are rid of greed, desire, fondness, thirst, passion, and craving for "
"form, when that form decays and perishes, will it give rise to sorrow, "
"lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress?”"

msgctxt "sn22.84:6.6"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.108"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.84:7.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, tissa."
msgstr "“Good, good, Tissa!"

msgctxt "sn22.84:7.2"
msgid "Evañhetaṃ, tissa, hoti."
msgstr "That’s how it is, Tissa,"

msgctxt "sn22.84:7.3"
msgid "Yathā taṃ rūpe vigatarāgassa …"
msgstr "when you are rid of greed for form …"

msgctxt "sn22.84:7.4"
msgid "vedanāya …"
msgstr "feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.84:7.5"
msgid "saññāya …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.84:7.6"
msgid "saṅkhāresu vigatarāgassa …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.84:7.7"
msgid ""
"viññāṇe vigatarāgassa vigatacchandassa vigatapemassa vigatapipāsassa "
"vigatapariḷāhassa vigatataṇhassa tassa viññāṇassa vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā "
"uppajjanti sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.84:7.8"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.84:8.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, tissa."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.2"
msgid "Evañhetaṃ, tissa, hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.3"
msgid "Yathā taṃ viññāṇe vigatarāgassa."
msgstr "consciousness."

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, tissa, "
msgstr "What do you think, Tissa? "

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.5"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.6"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.7"
msgid "“Vedanā …"
msgstr "“Is feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.8"
msgid "saññā …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.9"
msgid "saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.10"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.11"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.12"
msgid "“Tasmātiha … pe …"
msgstr "“So you should truly see …"

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.13"
msgid "evaṃ passaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Seeing this …"

msgctxt "sn22.84:8.14"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāti."
msgstr "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.84:9.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, tissa, dve purisā—"
msgstr "Suppose, Tissa, there were two people."

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.2"
msgid "eko puriso amaggakusalo, eko puriso maggakusalo."
msgstr "One was not skilled in the path, the other was."

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.3"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ so amaggakusalo puriso amuṃ maggakusalaṃ purisaṃ maggaṃ puccheyya."
msgstr ""
"The one not skilled in the path would question the one skilled in the path,"

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.4"
msgid "So evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "who would reply:"

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.5"
msgid "‘ehi, bho purisa, ayaṃ maggo."
msgstr "‘Come, good man, this is the path."

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.6"
msgid "Tena muhuttaṃ gaccha."
msgstr "Go down it a little,"

# Interesting use of muncati and ganhati.
msgctxt "sn22.84:9.7"
msgid ""
"Tena muhuttaṃ gantvā dakkhissasi dvedhāpathaṃ, tattha vāmaṃ muñcitvā "
"dakkhiṇaṃ gaṇhāhi."
msgstr ""
"and you’ll see a fork in the road. Ignore the left, and take the right-hand "
"path."

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.8"
msgid "Tena muhuttaṃ gaccha."
msgstr "Go a little further,"

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.9"
msgid "Tena muhuttaṃ gantvā dakkhissasi tibbaṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ."
msgstr "and you’ll see a dark forest grove."

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.10"
msgid "Tena muhuttaṃ gaccha."
msgstr "Go a little further,"

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.11"
msgid "Tena muhuttaṃ gantvā dakkhissasi mahantaṃ ninnaṃ pallalaṃ."
msgstr "and you’ll see an expanse of low-lying swampland."

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.12"
msgid "Tena muhuttaṃ gaccha."
msgstr "Go a little further,"

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.13"
msgid "Tena muhuttaṃ gantvā dakkhissasi sobbhaṃ papātaṃ."
msgstr "and you’ll see a large, steep cliff."

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.14"
msgid "Tena muhuttaṃ gaccha."
msgstr "Go a little further,"

msgctxt "sn22.84:9.15"
msgid "Tena muhuttaṃ gantvā dakkhissasi samaṃ bhūmibhāgaṃ ramaṇīyan’ti."
msgstr "and you’ll see level, cleared parkland.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.109"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.84:10.1"
msgid "Upamā kho myāyaṃ, tissa, katā atthassa viññāpanāya."
msgstr "I’ve made up this simile to make a point."

msgctxt "sn22.84:10.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ cevettha attho:"
msgstr "And this is what it means."

msgctxt "sn22.84:10.3"
msgid "‘puriso amaggakusalo’ti kho, tissa, puthujjanassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘A person who is not skilled in the path’ is a term for an ordinary "
"uneducated person."

msgctxt "sn22.84:10.4"
msgid ""
"‘Puriso maggakusalo’ti kho, tissa, tathāgatassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ arahato "
"sammāsambuddhassa."
msgstr ""
"‘A person who is skilled in the path’ is a term for the Realized One, the "
"perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha."

msgctxt "sn22.84:10.5"
msgid "‘Dvedhāpatho’ti kho, tissa, vicikicchāyetaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘A fork in the road’ is a term for doubt."

msgctxt "sn22.84:10.6"
msgid ""
"‘Vāmo maggo’ti kho, tissa, aṭṭhaṅgikassetaṃ micchāmaggassa adhivacanaṃ, "
"seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "‘The left-hand path’ is a term for the wrong eightfold path, that is,"

msgctxt "sn22.84:10.7"
msgid "micchādiṭṭhiyā … pe … micchāsamādhissa."
msgstr "wrong view … wrong immersion."

msgctxt "sn22.84:10.8"
msgid ""
"‘Dakkhiṇo maggo’ti kho, tissa, ariyassetaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikassa maggassa "
"adhivacanaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "‘The right-hand path’ is a term for the noble eightfold path, that is,"

msgctxt "sn22.84:10.9"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhiyā … pe … sammāsamādhissa."
msgstr "right view … right immersion."

msgctxt "sn22.84:10.10"
msgid "‘Tibbo vanasaṇḍo’ti kho, tissa, avijjāyetaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘A dark forest grove’ is a term for ignorance."

msgctxt "sn22.84:10.11"
msgid "‘Mahantaṃ ninnaṃ pallalan’ti kho, tissa, kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘An expanse of low-lying swampland’ is a term for sensual pleasures."

msgctxt "sn22.84:10.12"
msgid "‘Sobbho papāto’ti kho, tissa, kodhūpāyāsassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘A large, steep cliff’ is a term for anger and distress."

msgctxt "sn22.84:10.13"
msgid "‘Samo bhūmibhāgo ramaṇīyo’ti kho, tissa, nibbānassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘Level, cleared parkland’ is a term for extinguishment."

msgctxt "sn22.84:10.14"
msgid "Abhirama, tissa, abhirama, tissa."
msgstr "Rejoice, Tissa, rejoice!"

# Wow, that’s a major variant. It looks very much like a commentarial gloss.
#. VAR: Ahamovādena ahamanuggahena ahamanusāsaniyā”ti → ahamāmisadhammānuggahena mamovādena mamānusāsaniyāti (mr)
msgctxt "sn22.84:10.15"
msgid "Ahamovādena ahamanuggahena ahamanusāsaniyā”ti."
msgstr "I’m here to advise you, to support you, and to teach you.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.84:11.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn22.84:11.2"
msgid "Attamano āyasmā tisso bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti."
msgstr "Satisfied, Venerable Tissa was happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.84:11.3"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
